headline: What Cigna Group (CI)'s Alleged Rebate Diversion Class Action Means For Shareholders
summary: Earlier in February 2026, Bernstein Litowitz Berger & Grossmann LLP filed a class action alleging that Express Scripts, along with Cigna and Evernorth, diverted billions in drug rebates from pharmacy benefit manager clients to an offshore Swiss vehicle called Ascent through allegedly improper “fee” arrangements. The complaint claims this scheme conflicted with Express Scripts’ contractual obligations to pass through manufacturer rebates and to design formularies that prioritize cost...
